The paper discusses the DLVHEX system, which is a knowledge representation system that integrates answer set programming (ASP) with external sources. This makes it relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), databases (cs.DB), and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions real-world applications, which suggests a practical focus and further supports the relevance to cs.SE.
